Copy Assignment Operator

Definition:
The copy assignment operator is used to assign values from one existing object to another existing object.

ClassName& operator=(const ClassName &obj);

Returns *this to allow chained assignment (a = b = c;)

Default copy assignment does shallow copy.

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class MyClass {
public:
    int x;
    MyClass(int val = 0) : x(val) {}

    // Copy assignment operator
    MyClass& operator=(const MyClass &obj) {
        x = obj.x;
        cout << "Copy assignment called\n";
        return *this;
    }
};

int main() {
    MyClass a(5);
    MyClass b;
    b = a; // Copy assignment called
    cout << b.x << endl; // 5
}

âœ… Used when:

You assign one existing object to another.

